name: Bulbasaur
flavorTextEn: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

name: Ivysaur
flavorTextEn: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

name: Venusaur
flavorTextEn: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Charmander
flavorTextEn: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
flavorTextEn: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

name: Charizard
flavorTextEn: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

name: Squirtle
flavorTextEn: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

name: Wartortle
flavorTextEn: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

name: Blastoise
flavorTextEn: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

name: Caterpie
flavorTextEn: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Metapod
flavorTextEn: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

name: Butterfree
flavorTextEn: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

name: Weedle
flavorTextEn: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

name: Kakuna
flavorTextEn: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

name: Beedrill
flavorTextEn: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

name: Pidgey
flavorTextEn: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorTextEn: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Pidgeot
flavorTextEn: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

name: Rattata
flavorTextEn: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

name: Raticate
flavorTextEn: It uses its whis­ kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

name: Spearow
flavorTextEn: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

name: Fearow
flavorTextEn: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

name: Ekans
flavorTextEn: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

name: Arbok
flavorTextEn: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

name: Pikachu
flavorTextEn: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

name: Raichu
flavorTextEn: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

name: Sandshrew
flavorTextEn: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

name: Sandslash
flavorTextEn: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

name: Nidoran-f
flavorTextEn: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

name: Nidorina
flavorTextEn: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

name: Nidoqueen
flavorTextEn: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

name: Nidoran-m
flavorTextEn: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

name: Nidorino
flavorTextEn: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

name: Nidoking
flavorTextEn: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

name: Clefairy
flavorTextEn: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

name: Clefable
flavorTextEn: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

name: Vulpix
flavorTextEn: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

name: Ninetales
flavorTextEn: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

name: Jigglypuff
flavorTextEn: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff
flavorTextEn: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

name: Zubat
flavorTextEn: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

name: Golbat
flavorTextEn: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

name: Oddish
flavorTextEn: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

name: Gloom
flavorTextEn: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

name: Vileplume
flavorTextEn: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

name: Paras
flavorTextEn: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by draw­ ing nutrients from the bug host.

name: Parasect
flavorTextEn: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

name: Venonat
flavorTextEn: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

name: Venomoth
flavorTextEn: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

name: Diglett
flavorTextEn: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

name: Dugtrio
flavorTextEn: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

name: Meowth
flavorTextEn: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

name: Persian
flavorTextEn: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

name: Psyduck
flavorTextEn: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

name: Golduck
flavorTextEn: Often seen swim­ ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

name: Mankey
flavorTextEn: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

name: Primeape
flavorTextEn: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

name: Growlithe
flavorTextEn: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

name: Arcanine
flavorTextEn: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

name: Poliwag
flavorTextEn: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorTextEn: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

name: Poliwrath
flavorTextEn: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

name: Abra
flavorTextEn: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

name: Kadabra
flavorTextEn: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

name: Alakazam
flavorTextEn: Its brain can out­ perform a super­ computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

name: Machop
flavorTextEn: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

name: Machoke
flavorTextEn: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

name: Machamp
flavorTextEn: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

name: Bellsprout
flavorTextEn: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

name: Weepinbell
flavorTextEn: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

name: Victreebel
flavorTextEn: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

name: Tentacool
flavorTextEn: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

name: Tentacruel
flavorTextEn: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

name: Geodude
flavorTextEn: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

name: Graveler
flavorTextEn: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

name: Golem
flavorTextEn: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

name: Ponyta
flavorTextEn: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

name: Rapidash
flavorTextEn: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

name: Slowpoke
flavorTextEn: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Slowbro
flavorTextEn: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

name: Magnemite
flavorTextEn: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

name: Magneton
flavorTextEn: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

name: Farfetchd
flavorTextEn: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

name: Doduo
flavorTextEn: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

name: Dodrio
flavorTextEn: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

name: Seel
flavorTextEn: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

name: Dewgong
flavorTextEn: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

name: Grimer
flavorTextEn: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

name: Muk
flavorTextEn: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

name: Shellder
flavorTextEn: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

name: Cloyster
flavorTextEn: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

name: Gastly
flavorTextEn: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

name: Haunter
flavorTextEn: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an­ other dimension.

name: Gengar
flavorTextEn: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

name: Onix
flavorTextEn: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

name: Drowzee
flavorTextEn: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

name: Hypno
flavorTextEn: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

name: Krabby
flavorTextEn: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

name: Kingler
flavorTextEn: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

name: Voltorb
flavorTextEn: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

name: Electrode
flavorTextEn: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

name: Exeggcute
flavorTextEn: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

name: Exeggutor
flavorTextEn: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

name: Cubone
flavorTextEn: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON's real face.

name: Marowak
flavorTextEn: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

name: Hitmonlee
flavorTextEn: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorTextEn: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

name: Lickitung
flavorTextEn: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

name: Koffing
flavorTextEn: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

name: Weezing
flavorTextEn: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorTextEn: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.

name: Rhydon
flavorTextEn: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

name: Chansey
flavorTextEn: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

name: Tangela
flavorTextEn: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to sea­ weed. Its vines shake as it walks.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorTextEn: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

name: Horsea
flavorTextEn: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

name: Seadra
flavorTextEn: Capable of swim­ ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

name: Goldeen
flavorTextEn: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

name: Seaking
flavorTextEn: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming power­ fully up rivers and creeks.

name: Staryu
flavorTextEn: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

name: Starmie
flavorTextEn: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

name: Mr-mime
flavorTextEn: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

name: Scyther
flavorTextEn: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

name: Jynx
flavorTextEn: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

name: Electabuzz
flavorTextEn: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

name: Magmar
flavorTextEn: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

name: Pinsir
flavorTextEn: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

name: Tauros
flavorTextEn: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

name: Magikarp
flavorTextEn: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

name: Gyarados
flavorTextEn: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

name: Lapras
flavorTextEn: A POKéMON that has been over­ hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

name: Ditto
flavorTextEn: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

name: Eevee
flavorTextEn: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

name: Vaporeon
flavorTextEn: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

name: Jolteon
flavorTextEn: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.

name: Flareon
flavorTextEn: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

name: Porygon
flavorTextEn: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

name: Omanyte
flavorTextEn: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

name: Omastar
flavorTextEn: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

name: Kabuto
flavorTextEn: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

name: Kabutops
flavorTextEn: Its sleek shape is perfect for swim­ ming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorTextEn: A ferocious, pre­ historic POKéMON that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

name: Snorlax
flavorTextEn: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

name: Articuno
flavorTextEn: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

name: Zapdos
flavorTextEn: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

name: Moltres
flavorTextEn: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

name: Dratini
flavorTextEn: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

name: Dragonair
flavorTextEn: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

name: Dragonite
flavorTextEn: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

name: Mewtwo
flavorTextEn: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

name: Mew
flavorTextEn: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.

name: Chikorita
flavorTextEn: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.

name: Bayleef
flavorTextEn: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.

name: Meganium
flavorTextEn: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.

name: Cyndaquil
flavorTextEn: It is timid, and always curls it­ self up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

name: Quilava
flavorTextEn: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

name: Typhlosion
flavorTextEn: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Totodile
flavorTextEn: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.

name: Croconaw
flavorTextEn: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

name: Feraligatr
flavorTextEn: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

name: Sentret
flavorTextEn: A very cautious POKéMON, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.

name: Furret
flavorTextEn: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other POKéMON to enter.

name: Hoothoot
flavorTextEn: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Noctowl
flavorTextEn: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

name: Ledyba
flavorTextEn: It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.

name: Ledian
flavorTextEn: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.

name: Spinarak
flavorTextEn: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

name: Ariados
flavorTextEn: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.

name: Crobat
flavorTextEn: It flies so si­ lently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.

name: Chinchou
flavorTextEn: It shoots positive and negative elec­ tricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

name: Lanturn
flavorTextEn: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea's surface from a depth of over three miles.

name: Pichu
flavorTextEn: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

name: Cleffa
flavorTextEn: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

name: Igglybuff
flavorTextEn: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

name: Togepi
flavorTextEn: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togetic
flavorTextEn: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, car­ ing people and shower them with happiness.

name: Natu
flavorTextEn: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always star­ ing at something.

name: Xatu
flavorTextEn: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

name: Mareep
flavorTextEn: If static elec­ tricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Flaaffy
flavorTextEn: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Ampharos
flavorTextEn: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Bellossom
flavorTextEn: BELLOSSOM gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

name: Marill
flavorTextEn: The tip of its tail, which con­ tains oil that is lighter than wa­ ter, lets it swim without drowning.

name: Azumarill
flavorTextEn: By keeping still and listening in­ tently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast- moving rivers.

name: Sudowoodo
flavorTextEn: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composi­ tion appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.

name: Politoed
flavorTextEn: If POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL hear its echoing cry, they respond by gather­ ing from far and wide.

name: Hoppip
flavorTextEn: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.

name: Skiploom
flavorTextEn: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluc­ tuates up and down.

name: Jumpluff
flavorTextEn: Once it catches the wind, it deft­ ly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.

name: Aipom
flavorTextEn: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

name: Sunkern
flavorTextEn: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will violently shake its leaves.

name: Sunflora
flavorTextEn: It converts sun­ light into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.

name: Yanma
flavorTextEn: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter win­ dows in the area.

name: Wooper
flavorTextEn: This POKéMON lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
flavorTextEn: This carefree POKéMON has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

name: Espeon
flavorTextEn: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its ene­ my's actions.

name: Umbreon
flavorTextEn: When agitated, this POKéMON pro­ tects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.

name: Murkrow
flavorTextEn: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Slowking
flavorTextEn: It has incredible intellect and in­ tuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

name: Misdreavus
flavorTextEn: It likes playing mischievous tricks such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

name: Unown
flavorTextEn: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tab­ lets. It is said that the two are somehow related.

name: Wobbuffet
flavorTextEn: It hates light and shock. If attack­ ed, it inflates its body to pump up its counter­ strike.

name: Girafarig
flavorTextEn: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.

name: Pineco
flavorTextEn: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

name: Forretress
flavorTextEn: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

name: Dunsparce
flavorTextEn: When spotted, this POKéMON escapes backward by furi­ ously boring into the ground with its tail.

name: Gligar
flavorTextEn: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the star­ tled victim to inject poison.

name: Steelix
flavorTextEn: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.

name: Snubbull
flavorTextEn: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

name: Granbull
flavorTextEn: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If at­ tacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

name: Qwilfish
flavorTextEn: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

name: Scizor
flavorTextEn: It swings its eye- patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

name: Shuckle
flavorTextEn: The BERRIES it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

name: Heracross
flavorTextEn: This powerful POKéMON thrusts its prized horn under its enemies’ bellies then lifts and throws them.

name: Sneasel
flavorTextEn: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it sud­ denly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

name: Teddiursa
flavorTextEn: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

name: Ursaring
flavorTextEn: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen BERRIES.

name: Slugma
flavorTextEn: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

name: Magcargo
flavorTextEn: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

name: Swinub
flavorTextEn: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
flavorTextEn: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

name: Corsola
flavorTextEn: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.

name: Remoraid
flavorTextEn: It has superb ac­ curacy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.

name: Octillery
flavorTextEn: It traps enemies with its suction- cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

name: Delibird
flavorTextEn: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

name: Mantine
flavorTextEn: As it majestically swims, it doesn't care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

name: Skarmory
flavorTextEn: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

name: Houndour
flavorTextEn: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

name: Houndoom
flavorTextEn: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

name: Kingdra
flavorTextEn: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

name: Phanpy
flavorTextEn: It swings its long snout around play­ fully, but because it is so strong, that can be dan­ gerous.

name: Donphan
flavorTextEn: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough to knock down a house.

name: Porygon2
flavorTextEn: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

name: Stantler
flavorTextEn: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where real­ ity is distorted.

name: Smeargle
flavorTextEn: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

name: Tyrogue
flavorTextEn: It is always bursting with en­ ergy. To make it­ self stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

name: Hitmontop
flavorTextEn: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.

name: Smoochum
flavorTextEn: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

name: Elekid
flavorTextEn: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.

name: Magby
flavorTextEn: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

name: Miltank
flavorTextEn: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

name: Blissey
flavorTextEn: Anyone who takes even one bite of BLISSEY's egg be­ comes unfailingly caring and pleas­ ant to everyone.

name: Raikou
flavorTextEn: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

name: Entei
flavorTextEn: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Un­ able to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

name: Suicune
flavorTextEn: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

name: Larvitar
flavorTextEn: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

name: Pupitar
flavorTextEn: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.

name: Tyranitar
flavorTextEn: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: Lugia
flavorTextEn: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

name: Ho-Oh
flavorTextEn: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world's skies con­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.

name: Celebi
flavorTextEn: This POKéMON wan­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
